# Goal: determine which of the memory nomination stages will populate the subject's memory list
# When participants complete this survey and a re asked to generate 24 memories, they are provided
# with many "nomination stages". Participants are required to come up with 24 memories, or else they are
# not able to participate in the second session. These stages are different ways to help the participant
# think of 24 salient memories from their life. Some participants/testers have had trouble getting 24 memories,
# so providing with inspirations such as
# Think of your life story and provide memories that come to mind" (Life Story, LS),
# "Think of memories from you childhood years, teen years, adult years" (Life Periods, LP),
# "Think of other memories related to the memories you have already given us" (Memory-to-Memory, M2M),
# "Think of memories related to any of the following life events [list of common life events, incl. First Date or First Job]" (CLE).
